OL,3,CAre you set to benefit from the
OL,4,CChancellor's National Insurance cut?
OL,6,FBut it'll cost the Treasury an
OL,7,Festimated #10bn, with Labour arguing
OL,8,Fthe price will be cuts to public
OL,9,Fspending and tax hikes elsewhere.
OL,11,FSo are you set to benefit? And how
OL,12,Fmuch by?
OL,14,FEmployees and self-employed workers
OL,15,Fcurrently pay 10% on earnings between
OL,16,F#12,570 and #50,270 in Class 1
OL,17,FNational Insurance contributions.
