OL,3,CAre you set to benefit from the
OL,4,CChancellor's National Insurance cut?
OL,6,FFor the average worker earning
OL,7,F#35,000, reducing National Insurance
OL,8,Fto 8% would mean they have #449 extra
OL,9,Fin their pocket over the course of a
OL,10,Fyear.
OL,12,FFor someone earning #25,000 that's
OL,13,F#249 . And those on #50,000 it's #749.
OL,15,FBeyond that, any additional earnings
OL,16,Fare taxed at 2% and won't be affected
OL,17,Fby the cut to National Insurance.
