OL,4,CChancellor's National Insurance cut?
OL,6,FFor many the benefit of the tax cut
OL,7,Fwill be outweighed by the Treasury's
OL,8,Fdecision to freeze the salary
OL,9,Fthresholds for both National Insurance
OL,10,Fand income tax in cash terms.
OL,12,FCalculations by the Resolution
OL,13,FFoundation show only those paid
OL,14,Fbetween #27,000 and #59,000 would be
OL,15,Fbetter off off as a result of both the
OL,16,FAutumn Statement and Wednesday's
OL,17,FBudget, once the freeze in thresholds
OL,18,Fare accounted for.
OL,20,FHigher earners will be worse off by
OL,21,Faround #500.
